Raw Text:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1075
H.P. 697 House of Representatives, March 18, 2025
An Act to Require Annual Reporting Regarding the Low-income
Home Energy Assistance Program
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 14, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Housing and Economic Development pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed
pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative PERKINS of Dover-Foxcroft.
Cosponsored by Senator HARRINGTON of York and
Representatives: ARDELL of Monticello, BABIN of Fort Fairfield, FLYNN of Albion,
MCINTYRE of Lowell, MINGO of Calais, NUTTING of Oakland, Senators: CYRWAY of
Kennebec, GUERIN of Penobscot.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 30-A MRSA §4741, sub-§15, as amended by PL 2009, c. 372, Pt. B, §2, is
3 further amended to read:
4 15. State weatherization, conservation and fuel assistance agency. The Maine
5 State Housing Authority is designated the weatherization, energy conservation and fuel
6 assistance agency for the State and, in accordance with Title 35‑A, section 10104,
7 subsection 8, may apply for, receive, distribute and administer federal funds on behalf of
8 the State for weatherization, energy conservation and fuel assistance pursuant to the
9 Weatherization Assistance for Low-income Persons Program administered through the
10 United States Department of Energy and the Low-income Home Energy Assistance
11 Program administered through the United States Department of Health and Human
12 Services in accordance with rules adopted under the Maine Administrative Procedure Act;.
13 Beginning in 2026, the Maine State Housing Authority shall report annually to the joint
14 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing and economic
15 development matters on the Low-income Home Energy Assistance Program administered
16 through the United States Department of Health and Human Services in accordance with
17 Title 35-A, section 10104, subsection 8. The report must be for the fiscal year that
18 corresponds to the year funds were allocated and must include total funds disbursed,
19 amount of funds disbursed by fuel type, administrative costs to manage the program, a
20 detailed list of all funding sources and the total number of recipients of assistance by
21 county;
22 SUMMARY
2233 This bill requires the Maine State Housing Authority to report annually to the joint
2244 standing committee of the Legislature having jurisdiction over housing and economic
2255 development matters on the Low-income Home Energy Assistance Program administered
2266 through the United States Department of Health and Human Services. The report must be
2277 for the fiscal year that corresponds to the year funds were allocated and must include total
2288 funds disbursed, amount of funds disbursed by fuel type, administrative costs to manage
2299 the program, a detailed list of all funding sources and the total number of recipients of
3300 assistance by county.
